text:
News Kate Middleton looks sleek in royal blue coats as she arrives for first work engagement of the year Kate, who turned 35 on Monday, arrived this morning at the Anna Freud Centre where she is set to meet parents and children Share By Victoria Murphy Keyan Milanian 11:08, 11 JAN 2017 Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
The Duchess of Cambridge is back at work with two children's charity visits today. 
Kate, who turned 35 on Monday, arrived this morning at the Anna Freud Children's Centre Early Years Parenting Unit where she is set to meet parents and children under five and join in with a "theraplay" session. 
She was dressed in a sleek royal blue coat by British designers Eponine. 
Later, she and William will visit a Child Bereavement UK Centre in Stratford, London to mark its one year anniversary. 
The royals will meet families who have been helped by the charity when a baby or child is dying and children who have been helped after losing a parent. Read More (Photo: Rex Features) Prince William, Duke of Cambridge, is set to join Kate later today (Photo: WireImage) 
William became patron of the charity in 2009 and has particular empathy with its cause after losing his own mother, Princess Diana, when he was just 15. Read More Box for sale at Royal Albert Hall for Â£2.5million - that's TEN times more than the average house 
The Cambridges were criticised last year for being "work-shy" following the small number of engagements they carried out. 
But they have started back to work early this year and are expected to step up their duties in 2017. Like us on Facebook
